# AEM Copilot Setup - Installation Guide

## What's Included

### 1. `.vscode/mcp.json` — MCP Server Connections
- **Context7**: Live AEM/HTL/Granite UI documentation (no hallucinated APIs)
- **Playwright**: E2E testing and browser automation on localhost:4502/4503
- **Sequential Thinking**: Complex architecture decisions
- **Figma**: Design-to-code pipeline (needs Figma account)

### 2. `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — Project Rules
Teaches Copilot your AEM Cloud conventions: HTL syntax, BEM naming,
clientlib patterns, dialog XML, performance budgets, accessibility standards.

### 3. `.github/chatmodes/` — Sub-Agents (6 specialists)
- `htl-developer.chatmode.md` — HTL template generation
- `dialog-builder.chatmode.md` — Coral UI dialog XML
- `sass-developer.chatmode.md` — BEM SASS partials
- `js-developer.chatmode.md` — Clientlib-safe ES6 modules
- `test-writer.chatmode.md` — Jest + Playwright tests
- `code-reviewer.chatmode.md` — AEM best practices review
- `figma-to-aem.chatmode.md` — Figma design → full AEM component

### 4. `.github/prompts/` — Reusable Prompt Templates
- `create-component.prompt.md` — Generate complete component (all files)
- `create-dialog.prompt.md` — Generate dialog XML only
- `create-tests.prompt.md` — Generate unit + E2E tests
- `review-code.prompt.md` — Review code against AEM standards
- `figma-to-aem.prompt.md` — Convert Figma frame to AEM component

