## Installation Steps

### Step 1: Copy mcp.json
Replace your existing `.vscode/mcp.json` (or create it):
```
copy /Y ".vscode\mcp.json" "C:\tatapower\code\tp\.vscode\mcp.json"
```

### Step 2: Copy .github folder
```
xcopy /E /I ".github" "C:\tatapower\code\tp\.github"
```

### Step 3: Add .github to .gitignore (so it stays local only)
Add this line to your `.gitignore`:
```
.github/
.vscode/mcp.json
```

### Step 4: Verify MCP Servers in VS Code
1. Press Ctrl+Shift+P
2. Type "MCP: List Servers"
3. Start all 4 servers
4. Figma will ask for OAuth login on first use

### Step 5: Test a Chat Mode
1. Open Copilot Chat (Ctrl+Shift+I)
2. Click the model/mode selector at the top
3. You should see all 7 chat modes listed
4. Select "HTL Developer"
5. Ask: "Create an HTL template for a hero banner with title, description, and CTA"

### Step 6: Test a Prompt Template
1. In Copilot Chat, type `#`
2. You should see your prompt templates listed
3. Select "create-component"
4. Fill in the component name and fields

